26. From which body region does the right lymphatic duct collect lymph?
That's right!  These are the regions NOT drained by the thoracic duct.

2.1   Lymph from the Upper Right Quadrant

Lymph drainage from the upper right quadrant of the body is illustrated by the lighter shaded area in the accompanying diagram. 
Lymph from the right side of the head and neck drains via the right jugular trunk, lymph from the right upper limb and axilla drains via the right subclavian trunk, and lymph from the right thoracic contents drains via the right bronchomediastinal trunk. These converge on the right venous angle, often forming the right lymphatic duct before emptying into the right venous angle.
